## Component Patterns

1. Style files use `*.styles.ts` with `class-variance-authority` (CVA) variants.
2. Combine classes with `cn()` — do not build className strings manually.
3. Prefer existing design tokens (`var(--semantic-*)`, Tailwind preset) over raw hex/px values.
4. Export explicit public props interfaces. Keep internal-only types unexported.
5. Default exports are acceptable for components when stories or barrel files already rely on them.
6. Storybook stories live in `src/stories/` and import from the public barrel (`src/components/index.tsx`), not deep paths.

### CVA Example

```typescript
// Button.styles.ts
import { cva } from 'class-variance-authority';

export const buttonVariants = cva('inline-flex items-center justify-center', {
  variants: {
    variant: { primary: '...', secondary: '...' },
    size: { sm: '...', md: '...', lg: '...' },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'primary', size: 'md' },
});
```

```tsx
// Button.tsx
import { cn } from '@/services/utils';
import { buttonVariants } from './Button.styles';

export const Button = ({ variant, size, className, ...props }: ButtonProps) => (
  <button className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size }), className)} {...props} />
);
```
